# Documentation Workflow

After **any** code change, always update both living documents.

## README.md — update when

- New env variable added or renamed
- New API endpoint added
- New service or pipeline step introduced
- Docker/deployment instructions change
- Dependencies change

## DEVELOPMENT.md — append after every task

Use this format exactly:

```markdown
## [YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM] - TYPE

### Changes
- Bullet list of what changed

### Files Modified
- `path/to/file.py`

### Rationale
Why this change was made

### Breaking Changes
None  (or describe)

### Next Steps
What to do next  (optional)
```

**TYPE** is one of: `FEATURE` | `BUGFIX` | `REFACTOR` | `CONFIG` | `DOCS`

## .env.example — update when

Any new environment variable is added to `backend/app/core/config.py`.
Always add a commented example value; never a real secret.

## Checklist before finishing a task

- [ ] README updated (new features, endpoints, env vars)
- [ ] DEVELOPMENT.md entry appended
- [ ] .env.example updated (if new vars)
- [ ] No secrets committed
